    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-05-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="745"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d745">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Straus</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 118.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to ackowledge the receipt of your
                    confidential dispatch No. 73, of the 28th ultimo, containing an additional
                    report on the subject of the claims of American citizens against Turkey.</p>
                <p>Your action in the matter is approved by the Department, and the energy and
                    intelligence with which you are pressing for a settlement are commended.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
